Section 1:
1 L.D. 768
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 326, L.D. 768, “An Act to Update the
10 Laws Governing the Licensing of Intermediate Care Facilities for Persons with Intellectual
11 Disabilities”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1-A in the 3rd line (page 1, line 6 in L.D.) by
13 inserting after the following: "home" the following: 'nonnursing level'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 1-A in the 6th line (page 1, line 9 in L.D.) by
15 inserting after the following: "home" the following: 'nonnursing level'
16 Amend the bill in section 2 in §1812-B in the first indented paragraph in the 2nd line
17 (page 1, line 21 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "home" the following: 'nonnursing
18 level'
19 Amend the bill in section 2 in §1812-B in the first indented paragraph in the 5th line
20 (page 1, line 24 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "home" the following: 'nonnursing
21 level'
22 Amend the bill in section 2 in §1812-B in the first indented paragraph in the last line
23 (page 1, line 34 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "home" the following: 'nonnursing
24 level'
25 Amend the bill in section 4 in §1812-M in subsection 7 in the 2nd line (page 3, line 19
26 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "$2,000" and inserting the following: '$1,000'
27 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 5 and inserting the following:
28 'Sec. 5. 22 MRSA §8752, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2011, c. 542, Pt. A, §48, is
29 repealed and the following enacted in its place:
30 2. Health care facility. "Health care facility" or "facility" means a general or specialty
31 hospital including all facilities under the hospital's license, an ambulatory surgical facility,
32 an end-stage renal disease facility and a state institution as defined under Title 34‑B,
33 chapter 1, except that it does not include a facility licensed as a nursing facility or licensed
34 under chapter 1664.'
Page 1 - 132LR0260(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 326, L.D. 768
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment removes the provision in the bill that allows the delegation of the
55 administration of medication in nonnursing level intermediate care facilities for individuals
66 with intellectual disabilities. It also reduces the maximum license amount from $2,000 to
77 $1,000. It makes technical changes to the definition of "health care facility" in the sentinel
88 events statutes.
99 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1100 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR0260(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
